article.headline: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 73, Jackson St. 63
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Kevin Palmer scored 20 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Texas A&M-Corpus Christi to a 73-63 win over Jackson State on Friday at the South Padre Island Invitational. Justin Reynolds added 12 points and Filip Toncinic had 11 for A&M-Corpus Christi (2-3). The Islanders led only 36-34 at halftime but opened the second half with a 14-2 run. Palmer scored 16 of his 20 in the second half. Grant Maxey scored 22 points and had nine boards to lead Jackson State (0-5). Darion Griffin added 21 points.
